        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:49PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1249 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Reno, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Reno, Sparks, Stead, Lockwood, Damonte Ranch, Northwest Reno, Lemmon
Valley, Mogul, Golden Valley, Caughlin Ranch, Reno-Tahoe
International Airport, Hidden Valley, Somersett, Pleasant Valley,
Verdi-Mogul, Lemmon Valley-Golden Valley, Mustang, Nws Reno, Patrick,
and Sun Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
